  "text": "To investigate the molecular mechanisms of iron uptake and cell death of tobacco BY-2 cells, we identified and characterized several tobacco iron transporter genes. As the ZIP and NRAMP family proteins are known as iron/metal transporters in plants, we identified two tobacco cDNA clones that encoded proteins with high sequence similarity to ZIP or NRAMP and named them NtZIP1 and NtNRAMP1, respectively. The amino acid sequence of NtZIP1 was 61 % identical to the MtZIP3 of Medicago truncatula [CITATION_1] ) and 53 % to AtZIP5 of Arabidopsis thaliana, whereas NtNRAMP1 was 71 % identical to Arabidopsis AtNRAMP1 and AtNRAMP6. Gene expression analysis revealed that 1.0 mM FeSO 4 application increased the relative transcript levels of NtNRAMP1 but decreased those of NtZIP1 (Fig. 3A, B) .",
